MAB-Malware an open-source reinforcement learning framework to generate AEs for PE malware. We model this problem as a classic multi-armed bandit (MAB) problem, by treating each action-content pair as an independent slot machine.

OIKAN is a neuro-symbolic machine learning framework inspired by Kolmogorov-Arnold representation theorem. It combines the power of modern neural networks with techniques for extracting clear, interpretable symbolic formulas from data. OIKAN is designed to make machine learning models both accurate and Interpretable.

The goal is to automate the process of evaluating ontology consistency through machine learning models, ensuring that the ontologies meet the required logical structure.

ML-Air_quality is a project to analyze and predict air quality using machine learning. It loads datasets (pollutants, weather), preprocesses data, trains models to estimate AQI or detect pollutant trends, and validates results (MAE, RMSE) with visualizations, providing a reproducible framework.

MEDPRIV-AI Framework  A secure and privacy-preserving machine learning pipeline for healthcare data, developed for the ISBCardiff Hackathon. Combines Federated Learning and Differential Privacy to protect sensitive medical information.

Reinforce4j is a Java library designed for implementing reinforcement learning algorithms, with a primary focus on Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS). It provides tools and frameworks for building agents that can learn to play games, demonstrated with examples like Tic-Tac-Toe and Connect 4.
